[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring ClassLoader and Reflection**\n\nI'm considering whether we can avoid using reflection by employing ClassLoader instead. For running types from a separate ClassLoader, it seems we need to either reflect or cast if it's a parent class. If the child loads a separate copy, casting might not work. When using JUnit, it loads interfaces in a way that allows casting to work.\n\nI wonder if dynamic access through ClassLoader.loadClass might be a better focus than direct reflection, which we should avoid. Creating a URLClassLoader with library jar sounds useful, but how to find a version-agnostic jar path? I’ll need to think about this in terms of accessing resources like IntrospectorTestCase.class, while ensuring no hardcoded versions are involved.\n\n**Considering Access and Initialization Issues**\n\nI'm considering the challenge of accessing a package-private synthetic static field, which I can’t get to without using reflection, but that's forbidden. I wonder if I should resort to Unsafe, though that feels like a more direct and potentially worse method. Creating a test within the org.apache package isn't an option since the rule says to keep things outside library packages.\n\nI'm also contemplating whether the configuration related to native images is set up properly. Should the resource path actually be META-INF/native-image/group/artifact/native-image.properties? It seems like it might not just be one directory. I need to clarify this!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02c5ecfe2c10a6f30169ef744341ac8193997ab1c0a1806f3d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp73ROGreXxU2uJ3UewB7zUCCCvyvbCMxBjnyDminCBb8g7ppBhyhOH0MUGIKhuyXLV9by-Q6tdbib8BSapc7uUG8PP_vNf8jJcGGJU5ahFWoskeWhce0Bd5nQnu2n1_Ah5HS5dE7CP1k4SXhiMMCxsmY23_ESRGsRWFO6a5-2B7eC1FwARFMDdezMko6Xk9IZI9ZQ6BGPccC8paA_xbOzVUaAevshIr6FnSAFbgdXI-Cf40t9348BGOW9FABiDuz6QsabCgaTPxQaKzMLHKjolp